1. Use Environment Variables in Node-RED

In Render, go to Settings â†’ Environment and create variables:

Name	Value
TUYA_DEVICE_ID	    your device ID
TUYA_ACCESS_ID	    your Tuya Access ID
TUYA_ACCESS_SECRET	your Tuya Access Secret
TUYA_REGION	        your Tuya region (e.g., EU)
PUSHOVER_USER	      your Pushover user key
PUSHOVER_TOKEN	    your Pushover API token
